+## Agent 12 вҖ” Final Review and Cleanup (completed)
+
+### What was done
+
+**Review:** Full architectural review of the notification system built across 11 sessions. Verified compilation, test suite, adapter consistency, event coverage, preferences gating, and history logging.
+
+**Issue found and fixed: Missing user event handlers**
+
+`UserService` emitted `user:created` and `user:updated` events, and the notification types `user_welcome` and `user_updated` existed, but `NotificationService` had no handlers for them вҖ” user lifecycle notifications were silently dropped.
+
+**Fix:**
+- Added `handleUserCreated()` and `handleUserUpdated()` handlers in `NotificationService.registerHandlers()`
+- `user:created` вҶ’ sends a welcome email with the user's name
+- `user:updated` вҶ’ sends a profile update email listing changed fields
+- Added 2 tests covering both handlers
+
+**Other findings (no action needed):**
+- `in-app` channel is declared in `NotificationChannel` but has no adapter вҖ” this is fine as a future placeholder; the system gracefully records notifications even without an adapter
+- Adapter naming conventions differ per domain (e.g., `getSentEmails` vs `getSentMessages` vs `getSentWebhooks`; transport methods `deliver`/`send`/`post`) вҖ” these are intentional domain-appropriate names, not bugs
+- Some internal types (reset functions, `CallbackRegistry`, `EventHandler`, `DatabaseRecord`, `LogLevel`) are not re-exported from `src/index.ts` вҖ” these are internal/test utilities and don't need public export
+
+### System Architecture Summary
+
